<h2>🌏 Introduction</h2>

<p>
The <strong>:contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}</strong> is a small island nation in the <strong>central Pacific Ocean</strong>, located in the region of <strong>Micronesia</strong>. It consists of around <strong>29 coral atolls and 5 individual islands</strong>, spread over a very large ocean area.
</p>

<p>
It is known for its clear lagoons, coral reefs, remote islands, and strong connection with the United States. Despite its tiny land area, it controls a vast exclusive economic zone in the Pacific Ocean.
</p>

<p>
The economy mainly depends on fishing, U.S. assistance, shipping registry services, and limited tourism, along with growing focus on climate resilience and renewable energy.
</p>

